 <h3>Five Wishes &reg;</h3>
 <p style="text-align: left;">&ldquo;Five Wishes &reg;&rdquo; is an easy-to-use legal document written in everyday language to help you plan how you want to be cared for in case you become seriously ill. It is America&rsquo;s most popular living will.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>You decide:</strong> With more than 18 million copies in circulation, &ldquo;Five Wishes &reg;&rdquo; helps you express what you want in the areas that matter the most to you: personal, spiritual, medical and legal. It helps you describe what good care means to you, whether you are seriously ill or not, so your caregiver knows exactly what you want.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Gift to your family:</strong> &ldquo;Five Wishes &reg;&rdquo; can help start and guide family conversations in advance of serious illness, so completing it is a gift to your family, friends and also your doctor. It keeps them out of the difficult position of having to guess what kinds of treatment you want or don&rsquo;t want.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Meets Florida law:</strong> &ldquo;Five Wishes &reg;&rdquo; meets the legal requirements for an advance directive in Florida and 41 other states. All you need to do is check a box, circle a direction, or write a few sentences. Once it is signed and witnessed, your &ldquo;Five Wishes &reg;&rdquo; becomes a legal document.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">To learn more about &ldquo;Five Wishes &reg;&rdquo;or to schedule a presentation for your group or community, please email <a href="mailto:Cperry@treasurehealth.org" target="_blank">Craig Perry</a>&nbsp; in Martin County or <a href="mailto:tkinsley@treasurehealth.org" target="_blank">Tracey Kinsley</a> in St. Lucie County.</p>
